\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Could I ask you your name and present address please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Frederick - you want the full name? Frederick Arthur Julian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And your address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Number nine Swinton Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What's your marital status, are you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I'm a widower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Could you tell me your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 1927.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. 24th of January, 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - the place is gone now, at the top of the street here - Propect Terrace. W.C,1.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How many years did you live in the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I couldn't say. I was at the hospital eleven months. They took me to the hospital with - spinal trouble - tuberculosis of the spine.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You were only eleven months old then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How long were you in hospital before you came out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - after - I can remember up to about four years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did you live when you came out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Dig Road. Yes, W.C.1.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And you lived with your gran?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you live with your mother and father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Ten years of age - I had to go home. Also I was getting a bit big and my - my gran only had one room, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So you lived with your gran from the time you came out of hospital to about ten years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And then you went to live with your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How long were you with your family then, you went with your family when you were ten years old, how long did you live with them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I lived them til I was about - fourteen. I used to have wear a - jacket you know for me spine, and - I got a job at - in a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564  boot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 shop, in Eric and Butts, Elephant and Cattle. At nine shillings a week. Used to do twelve hours a day. Sixteen on a Friday and about eighteen on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did you live after you started work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I lived in St. Gabriel Street, Elephant and Castle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You found digs did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
No, me mother moved over there. See, I were fourteen at the time - I left school before - I should have left school. And I was supposed to go into a - like to learn a trade for watch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 making - and boot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 m
aking. I didn't want it. I wanted to - find me own way. Anyway the - war come, and - I believe me father just come out the - the Army about 1915, in the Army before the war. Any rate - he got me a job down at Winchester on Aerodrome work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So that took you up to the end of the war more or less did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes. And then when I come back I went back to live with me granny again, she had a - house by an uncle who started up from a - little coal shop, rubber merchant, and he had a big place in Gee Street, Euston - Singwell Street, just off of Euston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
When your family moved when you were ten years old, do you remember why they moved? Was it to get a bigger house or because of your father's job, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I can't - I know t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 hey moved into - place in - Cha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 pel Street, where the market is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But you don't know why they did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I had a - five brothers and four sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Could you tell me their birth order or their ages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well - I had - me older brother got killed in New Cross in the war. He was about - oh - about fifty - fifty-four then, well how long has the war been over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What order did they come in, a boy was the oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Boy - one, two - one, two
 - two boys. A girl. A boy, that's me. Three younger sisters. And a - another boy. Eight. Well there - I believe there was one born, but he died before me - eldest brother died, I don't - don't know nothing about him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were they pretty regularly spaced, every one or two years or was there a bigger gap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
About - there's two - born within twelve months of each other. The others - well - brother died about forty-year ago, he was seventy-three. I've got a brother older than me now, he's fifty - older t
han me, he's seventy-five. Seventy-five. Sister - is - seventy-three. And I'm seventy. Then I had a sister - about eleven months - eleven months younger than me. Then there's another one - about three years younger than her. And the other one's about - oh
 - seven years younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Seven years younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about the youngest boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well he - he died - I think he was - while the war was - 1914 war, at the end of the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 1917 or '18 or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you know how old your father was when you were born? Or how old he was when he died?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well he was about - eighty - I think it was eighty - five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What year did he die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - I try to think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you know whe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 re he came from, was he a Londo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 ner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 A Londo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
ner, yes. He come from - just from - round by Regents Park. Little - Little Welby Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about his occupations, you say he was a regular soldier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Before the war. The Queen's Own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you know how long eh was in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well he was in there during the Boer War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And he stayed in the Army right through to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. I believe he were called up you know, being on the reserved list or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So in 1911 he would have been a soldier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you know what he did before he went in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well - his people were - oh well, I can't go back to that, it's a long way you see. His - all his people were all off, and they left him - like a business. And - he's one of the
se men about town like - King Edward - was at the time. Galloping about with these - ponies and going race meetings and that. And - when he come back - all his horse - these pony carts what they call 'em were all dead in stables. And that's the sort of ma
n he was. He - if me mother liked to have left - left him, she could have gone and lived with our - one of her sisters, who was well off at the time, but she wouldn't leave him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So he'd been left a bit of money in his early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. And he gallivanted about and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What did he do after 1918, when he came out of the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well - he put in a couple of claims - for - told him he was going - costermonger for a a while and they give him a - security you know, and he - started up a little business again and that went broke. And - I can't think what he done afterwards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7619679\charrsid6116564 Mainly cost-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 mongering type things though was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Well that's what he used to put down - put himself down as a costemonger. Yes. Like - when I got married, he was
 witness, costermonger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How old was your mother when you were born, was she older of younger than your dad do you know or about the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I think she'd be younger than me - father. I think she was about - forty-nine when she died. Died of cancer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you know what year this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh, I can't think. No. Somewhere about - 1919, 1920 sometime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Just shortly after the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well actually her - her father was born in County Down - 
Ireland. And her mother was born here, but she's from Irish parents. So me mother's side are Irish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But she was born in London herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did she work before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. She used to - have a couple of jobs, like out 
in service. She worked with the Duchess of Marlborough, in Bedford Place. And - used to come round - used to go out and do a bit of cleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So she just worked at this place during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 She carried on working after she was married did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 The same sort of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Same you know. Duchess of Marlborough, she was - oh - she reckoned she - she were a young - girl you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was this just general domestic work or was she a cook or a maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I think it was - like cleaning you know, dusting, you know, all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Who looked after the children while your mum was at work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well they - had to look after theirselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How many rooms were there in the house with your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well it was a big house but she only had two rooms herself. You know, like a back room, what you call a kitchen. And a front bedroom.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did anyone besides your grandmother and yourself live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I had a uncle live up - just u
p - couple of doors away, name of - like a - a daughter, and a son-in-law, and he was a - a business man himself. A silver - a gold and silver smith. He had his - like a bike shop, motor bikes and all that at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But never actually lived in the house with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. Not - people lived in the house but not - nothing to do with us, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 It was done at home. My granny used to do - do the washing. In fact - I remember her taking in washing - for other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did she used to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Downstairs in the copper you know. Had a copper downstairs, in the kitchen - in the - what do they call them, the wash house they call 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was this like one of these tenement buildings you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Ordinary house you know - like first floor, second floor, you know up - up to about the fourth floor. Quite a big house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And had the washrooms downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 YES.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What about toilet facilities, did you share those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, toilet was at the bottom of the - right - down - the yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was your grandmother on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, well her - her husband died when I were about - five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So you wouldn't remember much about your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. I remember he used to take me - in the pub w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1654254\charrsid6116564 
ith him, called the Kentish Arm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
s. That's also - Grosvenor Terrace, where the sawdust used to be on the floor and the - spit bowls used to be - I remember I used to go and play on the floor. And - a lot of 'em couldn't understand when h
e used to talk. But I could understand him. They told me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Can you remember anything else about your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 About me...? Well he was a - a master builder. You see that big station at St. Pancras, well he worked on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your grandmother make or mend any of your family's clothes do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - only darning socks and that but I can't think about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Actually making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were your clothes new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1654254\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - usually new because - suits in them
 times - cost about - four and six. And you'd get a pair of shoes for about - two and nine. Or boots we used to wear. But I used to have a lady, being a cripple - Mr Iting, he used to send me - boxes of sweets every month, Scout books - overcoats if I wan
ted in the winter or - shoes or boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How did this lady know about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
The - cripple schools, we had doctors and - sisters there - in Grosvenor Place. Called St Mary's Well now. And - I suppose - that the ladies used to come - visit. And we cou
ldn't - we wasn't allowed to walk. And we used to have go by - by ambulance. Used to pick us up on the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So you did receive a bit of help from this lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have any tasks that you had to do to help your grandmother in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
YES. Like cleaning the stairs, or the knives and forks and - like - when I went home when I was ten, well - me father used to give us all - something to do. One had the stairs. One had the room. One had the knives and forks. All sorts of 
- things like that. And he used to sit and - and watch us, me father. He never used to do a thing. But we had to do it all. Of course I think it was a good thing. In a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And your father wouldn't help your mother with anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. 
I've never known - I tell you, I've never known him to go to work or do anything. My mother used to keep the lot of us I think. Of course I know what it is - to be hungry. When I went home, before that - my granny, she had a son, and a - a daughter-in-law
 next door used to help her, you see, I mean she was never short of anything. And I never - went short until I went home. I remember to cry many a time being hungry when I got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 At this time before 1918 though was your father at home very much if he was in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well, no, he used to come - on leave now and again. But - I went back - sometime - after the war - to my granny's again. Of course she had a bigger place. Outside Euston station - 'til this war started and 19 - 1939, of course I wa
s married - in between - then. As I told you in - 19 - 27. And - in 1939 I - give it up and joined the A.R.P., City of London Corporation. And they give me a regular job. And I then I had to - migraine used to come on. I - I told you I've had about thirty
-two operations in my time. Although I can't think of - I know the last - ten that I've had. I've had two on the year, one on the eye. Knee. Any road -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Going back to when you were with your grandmother at ten years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, ten o'clock. Go to bed at ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did she used to put you to bed or did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I used to put myself to bed, when I - you know, I was getting on. When I got to ten years of age, see only having the one \endash 
 bed, a big bed she had, when I got to ten I had to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You used to share the bed with your grandmother until then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well we never had no bath. No. Used to have to take you down the stairs with the copper was and - in a tub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How often would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well every week, every Saturday night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 This was a regular routine was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Can we now talk about the domestic routine between the ages of ten and fourteen when you went back home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was your father at home much during this period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well he used to come home now and again you know like. Oh leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 He was stationed in London somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes. I think it was - that big place. Salisbury plain. 'Cos I went to visit him, my mother took me there to see him once, all in the mud and slush and everything there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How many rooms were there in the house you were living in between ten and fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well there were only two rooms. Like a front room and a - back room, big - you know, a big room. And - when me brother was there and me, we used to have to sleep in the back room. And the girls used to sleep in the - same bed as - me mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How did you manage when your father came home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I think we used to sleep in the same bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was there anyone else besides your brothers and sisters living in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes - there was a married couple - at the top of the house, had one boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But they didn't actually have lodgers or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. She couldn't afford to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your mother do the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 She done her washing at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your mother or father make or mend any of the family clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well only you know - make trousers and that you know. I had a brother that used to mend our boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 The older brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
No. The one who's - I say, seventy-five now, now be seventy-six. Of course he - he was going to school - he was going to school at Manchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about clothes while you were at home, were these new or second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well second hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well we sometimes get - like - tickets from the school, to buy our - boots, used to be boots with the - eye tags you know, oh they couldn't pull - because they knew where they come from. There used to be plenty - plenty of pawns done then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So these were actually marked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did this lady, Mrs Iting, did she still help you when you went back home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, she used to - send me - parcels and - you know, tins of biscuits or sweets, butterscotch and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So she helped you out all through your childhood more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes. I used to go and see the Lord Mayor every Christmas - you see, at the Masnion House, and we'd presented with a big - hamper. Well there was - was a Christmas pudding, chicken, a
nd all that, all currant cake you know, that sort of thing. You'd see them all sitting at the big long table all in their robes and everything. Had to go to 'em and get it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was this for all the cripple children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 All - all the cripple children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 That must be quite an occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes, well I could - I could go there now, that's working - in the City, for fifty years. See. I only got the sack because - they thought I was unsuitable, you know, being very dangerous. Well sometimes - they want
 you to go out and sweep the roads and all that. I have, I've been a - plumber's mate, fitters mate. And during the war I was - in the A.R.P.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And you say your father wouldn't do anything at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. I can't remember him ever doing any work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would he do things like bringing the coal up or making a fire or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
No, he used to sit at the window with his Guards shirt on, and his packet of Players there, at the window, people used to think what a nice man he was. He had a
 nice blue suit, and South African boots. And - of course there used to be a lot of gambling in the streets then, you know, pitch and toss. And when they see him come they used to all run. They thought it was a policeman. And - I'm saying, he was a very n
ice looking man. Well built. In fact, he put you mind of - Hindenburg, you know, the - in Germany. Somehow, when I used to look at him I - I've got an idea that he - come from German blood. Being the name Julian and looking the appearance of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about dealing with the children, would he ever tell you stories or read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did he ever used to take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Or look after you when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 He was just waited on and looked after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes, we had to look after ourselves. The only time he used to be with us was Saturday when you was made to do all this work. One the stairs, one the stove - one the knives and forks. And sometimes if he got a bit wild with one of you his two
 fingers would tap you across the - ear. No, he wasn't a very good man. I say that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Some men had this idea that they shouldn't do anything didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Years ago. Years ago. Lots of men used to be like him. All they think about getting in the p
ubs and - I'll tell you one thing about him. They reckon he was the finest skittle player - in this country. And - he used to on Bushill Park here, and bowl his cheese, they called 'em cheese, twenty-eight pound, knock all his skittles down, run for about
 
three mile, have a drink on the way and come back and they still had to knock 'em down. And another time - my granny was telling me - that he was playing a man up at Aston - up - Vennel Park, and they all came with their ponies and traps y-ou know, just l
ike Derby day. All had their money on him, thought it was a cert he would win. But in between \{BLANK\}, and he lost the game. But he never come back to London for about nine or ten months afterwards. That's the sort of man he was. Horrible man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Amongst 
you children did the older ones used to help the younger ones with the things they found difficult, did they help them dress and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, yes, we used to like - the girls bit older than the other girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You'd help each other out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I mean to say, when I went home I was old enough to look after meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would the young children run any errands for the older ones and things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So you'd muck in together more or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. We as young ones used to help one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about bedtime while you were at home, did you have a regular bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Oh yes. Father used to holler out - window, if he - we darent' make a noise in the street or we were up to bed at four in the afternoon. But - we had our regular time. Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Your mother used to see you had a regular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have a bathroom here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. We had to wash down - like at the sink in the room. And a little we had to wash down - in that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How often would you have clean clothes at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well we should have 'em every week - mother used to - like do the washing, see that we were clean..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - our father used to sit down at the table and 
have his first. We used to sit on the couch. Very likely give us all a bit of bread and dripping each, and we had to sit there and watch him - and when he was done, we used to all have to get up to the table afterwards. All had our places to sit. All had 
- had regular things like that you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was this in the back room, the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, no, kitchen, well - we used to have it like in the front room where the - bed was. We had a table in there, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And you always ate in that room did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well she had the stove in the - kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What sort of stove was it, was it gas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was gas, yes. One of them old Holland ones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you remember what time breakfast was eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 W
ell we - had to be at school by - nine. I don't know what it was, two - or three girls, I'm not sure, used to go to school in the street. Used to go there, see. But I used to have to go - a little way further to George's Road, to wait for the ambulance. S
o we used to have our breakfast by about - quarter past eight to half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What members of the family were present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well there was - me oldest brothers - like, and - I can't remember me father ever being there. Me mother woul
d go out to work you see, to work about seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So you children would get your own breakfast would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well the eldest, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What did you usually have to eat and drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well we'd have a cup of tea and a - bit of bread and m
arg or - bit of bread and dripping. I used to have meals at school like, dinners and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have anything different on certain days, how about Sunday breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, we just had the ordinary you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You say you used to have your midday meal at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about your brothers and sisters, how did they get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well I think they used to come home. Very likely - get a fish and chips or something like that. Or - herrings, you know, 'course - you could get - seven pou
nd of potatoes then for about a penny farthing. I mean to say - a loaf of bread, penny farthing, with a - nearly half a - loaf cut in half for makeweight. Sometimes you had to go down Pic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564 c}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 adilly with a pillowcase, three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 penn'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 rth of stale, what they call - well, it's probably stale, be cakes and everything in it. Big pillowcase full for three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 pence. Sometimes you'd go down and ask in Smithfield market, three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 penn'orth of pieces. Well today cost you about - three pound for some of the stuff what we got then for three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You'd get some really good bits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. That used to be on a Friday, to last over Saturday and Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What would you have for your evening meal? Was this the main meal of the day when you got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Ordinary days. I tel
l you. We just had this bit of - like bread and dripping or - bit of bread and jam or something like that. Always. But on a - Sunday, well they - might send out for a pint of winkles or something, and give us a couple each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What would you have Sunday midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - might have bit of corned beef and - lettuce or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When did you used to eat these pieces you'd get from Hart's then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, we used to go down - on a Friday - night, when it - about six o'clock when they were
 pack - ready to - clear their stuff up. Of course I mean to say - on Saturday the markets used to keep open 'til about - half past eleven at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When would your mother cook these then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well she'd cook 'em like - on the Saturday morning or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So you'd have a cooked meal Saturday midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. What was - what was left was put away like - for Sunday's dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your mother bake her own bread or make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. I mean jam was cheap enough - to by, used to get the good half or cupful for about a ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did she bottle any fruit or make pickles or anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, she never had no time for anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about any homemade wines or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, no. Oh, I'll tell you what. For a 
cough or anything - she used to buy - some brown sugar - I can't think of the - mixture she used to mix with it. And she used to put half a turnip on top of it, and used to keep for about three or four days, used to go like a jelly. That was for coughs or
 anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you grown any of your own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, we never had no garden. No. Just a back yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did they buy tinned or dried vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I can't ever remember seeing - 'til - after the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You bought all fresh fruit did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Well - it was cheap enough. Used to get oranges for about sixteen for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you keep any livestock for the family, any hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I was at school - I can say that I had - practically nigh had it every day - myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about when you were on holiday from school, how often you'd have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, well, we used to belong to - places this 'ere, one up - the road here called Farrow 
Lane, we used to call it Fill Lane Flats. They used to give us tickets - to go - on outings in the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564  horse}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
brakes at the time. And - like day's outings. But - I can only remember again - on holiday once. Well I don't know whether it was holiday. But - it was by the seaside, it looked like a home to me, with sisters and nurses. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5395230\charrsid6116564 We had to sleep out on the veranda}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 . And all the time I was there I was crying to come home. I don't know how long I was there, I know it was a long while.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 It sounds like a recuperation place doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
That's right. I've seen a place like that down at Margage. And I've got an idea - that it's the place, you know, it seemed to hit me memory, when I walked by it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about tinned meat, how often did you eat tinned meat do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I don't remember ever eating tinned meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 We - used to buy it loose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well me mother used to eat less meat, used to see that we had - what she could afford. Herself - she used to eat very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Then he'd have a good meal. A big haddock or something like that. And sit down and eat that, always look after his self.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 He'd have something like this while you just had bread and marg or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. We had to sit on the couch - all of us. If there was bread and dripping very likely he'd give us it,
 and - we'd have to eat and - not say a word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well we were given like - the meals were put out. And you had to eat whatever was put out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the table, on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well they'd think you've had enough but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 They didn't make you eat it or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well that's what we used to have to do. If our father were watching. Have to - pass it round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I doubt if there was a second helping. You see,
 they only used to give us what - they was - well what me mother could spare, used to give us all. I think that we used to - like - help ourselves to the bread and dripping and a cup of tea and - any - thing to fill us up you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But could you ask if there was anything there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 We could do if mother - but not while me father was there. I think we were frightened to ask for anything while father was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, yes. You got to - like - put the - knife into the left hand or your fort in the right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. We had to go into - like - my bedroom if I wanted to - read or anything. How
ever at school - I couldn't read, write or tell the time or anything. 'Course - the cripple school where I went, all they learnt you was like - mat making, basket work, woodcarving. In fact I wanted to be a carpenter mostly, in me time, but - I just didn'
t have the chance to. But I learnt meself to read, write - I read tons of - tons of - history books.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You had to do all this after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, see, what it was - I may be at school for about - two or three months, and then - 
the doctor might say, you know, like - to me granny or - I had to go to the hospital, I've even heard her say, well we won't be long. Used to go out and there - I was left there - with the nurses and put into bed. And I'd be in there a - few months or so.
 Time after time that used to happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When were you allowed to leave the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well when we were all finished - when - we were - we used to have to say, excuse me, may I leave the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I
 think my father say his prayers. I don't know why he should but did though. I suppose he thought - I've got to forgive him you know. I don't know whether he believed it because - if he was - being a bad man like he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When did he say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Night time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would he say it at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did all the family sit down at the table for a meal, your father had his on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Had his on his own, and get up. And sit on the chair by the side of the window. And then me m
