\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Can you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Before 1918, yes, me grandfather. I remember - being Irish, having a wake. Standing the coffin up in the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 About how old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I must have been about - four, four and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And you still remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes, oh well, I can remember him - taking me by the hand, on a Sunday he used to go to this pub called the Kentish Arms, and - used to play on the fl
oor you know, lot of other children used to be in the pub then. And they used - never used to turn out 'til twelve o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you remember what happened at the funeral, were there many people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, all - the aunts and - on his si
de, come over from Ireland and that. And - had the - horses with the - plumes on their backs. And - Kensal Green he'd have it, and I remember in the church - all the choirboys walking round with big - sort of like - bars on there with candles. And playing
 - the hymns and hat. And coming home - coming home, pull up at the half way house and go in the pub and have a drink.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or relatives very much, or friends? You say your gran used to take you at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Ye
s. Used to just take me to me - like - when I lived in Derrick Road - I remember being on the old horse buses, going to the Elephant and Castle. Think - Newington Butts. Going through the City.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, I used to go
 - with me gran sometimes. She never used to get ready 'til about - nine o'clock on a Saturday night. She used to wear one of them - capes with a bonnet. All the sequins, weren't they? And - I used to stand up - in the middle of the town, while she get he
r
 shopping, what you call it now, buy, buy, buy, you know, and fishmongers and all that. And I used to stand near the - where they used to play the records. The Edison Bell it was run by. And I'd stand there for about - and hour or an hour and a half, list
ening to them play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 The streets used to be quite busy late at night then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Oh yes, there'd be terrific. And it wouldn't start closing in 'til about half past twelve - then. In fact, I've been - when I was - started work - at fourteen, I remember c
oming home - and going into a shop at half past one in the morning and buying myself a packet of - Park Drives, ten for tuppence ha'penny. Yes, some shops never used to shut 'til about two and half past two in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you ever remember going out with just you father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. I don't think he ever took us out. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
With your father being stationed at Salisbury wouldn't it have been easier for the family of have lived down there, do you know why you stayed in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, well - you know - Well I can't - I can't think why we - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you remember any outings with your parents, Bank Holidays or things like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I used to - I had a uncle that had a - a pony - you know, a cart of course, and they used to take us in - 
like - the family, to very likely Hampstead or - what do they call that - Blackheath - fairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you go away for a holiday during your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I remember once - and that was a - aunt who I told you lived next door to us in - Duk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6184572\charrsid6116564 e Road, Annie Martin, my granny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
's daughter. And he had the motorbike. I told you a gold and silver smith he was, his trade. And - I remember going to the seaside with them. And I - I couldn't say where the seaside was but I remember the - sky was blue and the sea
 was a lovely and blue you know. I've never seen anything like it. And it sometimes sticks in my and sometimes, to think of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Have you any idea how old you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I could have been about - six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You don't know whether it was for a day or a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I suppose it was - I was there - for a decent while, about a week I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were any other members of your family with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, just me aunt and - me grandmother and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How did you used to spend Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well - as - when I done me work like - might be about - two. I used to go out and meet some of the other boys and - well we used to play football in the street then. 'Cos the traffic was - isn't like it is today. You could go across from one road to an
other. And - sometimes play cricket and that you know like in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well Sunday sometimes - I used to go to church with me granny. Or like go for - like - to me aunts - on a night time about six o'clock. More likely come home about nine or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about when you lived at home, what would you do on Sunday then, did you still go to church then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 We didn't much - go to church much, in that time. We used to go - to a - Italian - church in Exmouth Street, next to the market.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was this a Roman Catholic church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But I'm Church of England myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you Church of England as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Me granny - I believe me grandfather was a - a Catholic. But me granny was - Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you ever go to Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was this Church of England Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I don't know, I don't know what - whether it was Church of England. I - St Pancras church in - Eu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6184572\charrsid6116564 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 ton Road, do you know it? Church in Euston Road there where - that'
s where we used to live, in flats. That's right. And that's where I was - christened, that was the Church of England, and - me granny knew the Father there, you know, used to take me there like, Sunday school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I can't remember me - father or mother ever going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What denomination were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I believe me father was Catholic and me mother was Catholic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yet your granny brought you up Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Well I suppose - me living with her, and she had her - way of - her own -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about playing games on Sunday, did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. Used to play rounders and - all that sort of thing. Hopscotch and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, I don't think we did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were there any Sunday school outings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, always a - one down here at - they used to call it Field Lane fete - Fild - Fild Court is it, just up the end here in Roseb
ery Avenue. We used to go there sometimes and they used to issue a - ticket - like, for an outing. We'd go to - we used to call it Lousy Loughton. Different, you know, different outings. I remember once on a - coach, horse coaches then, and a - boy holler
ing out - Crippin arrested. It was when they first had the - wireless, and sent it to the ship. I went on a - of course I - I think it was a Sunday in May - be a Saturday or - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What other social activities organised by the church or chapel did
 you take part in? Was there anything other than Sunday school outings, was there a Boys Brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well I was in Boys Brigade for a little while but - I don't think it was long. But - it - you know, I might be - out of hospital for about - three month
s and then I'd be back and - all I can remember, when I came to hospital - me mother and me gran saying, we won't be long, used to leave me there. I knew they - they'd gone and left me. And then they start undressing me and bathing me and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How often could parents visit you in hospital then or your granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh me gran used to come practically every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did they allow her to visit you for long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. Just for a - half an hour at a time. And they allowed one in the ward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did the church or chapel run a temperance club can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, I don't know of one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were there any other clubs you belonged to at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well in old - in - as I got older I belonged to the - Magdalen Club - run by Oxford University. That's when I 
was a bit older you know. I was about eighteen. Eighteen, after the - first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - when I was with me granny I used to have to say me prayers - at night before I got into bed. But I don't remem
ber - when I was home. Although I do say 'em you know, like now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you ever say prayers together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Can you remember if your father took an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, I don't think he did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, she - she was too busy - doing all the - jobs what she used to do, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Can you remember either of them voting before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No I can't really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well me mother was either doing a bit of work in the house and - if me father wasn't indoors he'd be out somewhere you know. In the - pub somewhere, or something like that. Where he used to get the money from - don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did she have any other leisure activities besides having a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Me mother? Well I don't - I don't think she ever had a drink herself. Only me father. No, no. Me mother used to - in the house, do anything in the house. Bit of work you know like cleaning and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 She was always working was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. As I said, she was our mother and our father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How often was your father home on leave, you would only see him when he was home on leave and he'd be there all day would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes. Yes. We used to live right next door - to a - public house, he was more in there. He used to play billiards a lot, or snooker you know and that. And - as I told you he was a - a good skittle player. They reck
on one of the finest. I've had men pull me out - old men - when I was a bit younger and say - ask me whether I was a - a relation of Harry Julian. And when I said, yes, they used to tell when they used to stand up the skittle for him, and they used to get
 
about - guinea - for standing them up for him. Yes. Well I remember going - like - into a free hour at the hospital, where the surgeon, with all the students all the way round and they used to throw a guinea on the floor, and this 'ere revolving - stage, 
m
e gran used to be there with me. He had a blackboard. After you pick up the guineas, or they back you to - you - if I done it now you see it - and - he used to rite me bet down on the - like - what it was supposed to be, and all these students could see y
ou and you sued to come round, you're more like - and that guineas he used to give me at the finish of the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So they were quite sympathetic and understanding of children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. I - well I think doctors in them times had more - I thi
nk they had more patience with people - and the nurses and sisters, I think were - better then - in them days, although they were hard worked, than they are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 On the whole you were fai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6184572\charrsid6116564 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 ly happy in hospital were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. But I always wanted to get home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would your mother ever go with your father when he went out playing skittles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. NA. no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your father take part in any other sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Not to my - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would he go to the races or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well, yes, yes, used to go - well, when he was young - when he used to - well, from what my gran tells me - that his father had a big business and left them all - some each like. He was a real right - wholesale - a butcher, his father was. And he l
eft 'em all - like - something in his will. Me father had - horses or bobs they used to call 'em. And - he used to go to races, anyway went to races and - when he come back these horses was - dead in the stable. Must have been away for about - a week or a
 fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Did your mother or father belong to any savings clubs do you know, any of these penny a week funeral clubs or sick clubs, anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, don't think so because - money was very hard in them times. I mean to say - if you were 
left a shilling you could get tiddly for two for a shilling at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, I used to see 'em now and again you know. Well we wasn't so far away. When I lived in Duke Road, you see, I - just 
up Eastham Street, used to go and see 'em, and we'd go back home again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was there one you felt particularly close to or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - I had a brother - he was - youth boy champion of - like youth boy of all these clubs, different clubs from all ro
und. He was the bantam weight champion of the clubs. I used to go with him sometimes to the - was number sixty-eight, I used to watch him scrubbing the forms and - tables. There was a chap behind the counter, used to be like a canteen, give me a basin of 
soup, and a bit of bread, while he was doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 As a child who did you play with most, your brothers and sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I can always remember being on me own. 'Til me - aunt next door - had a girl. And - when she was getting on like
 - she was about - four, and I were about - eight - we used to play with one another like. With the hoops and skipping ropes and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you think you were le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 t on your own a bit by the other children because of your disability?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, I had plenty of friends at school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 It was just that you preferred to play alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well me granny - never used to take much notice you know. Give me a wash down when I got home if I was a bit dirty and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about when you were at home, was that much the same there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Much the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did you play mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well in the street you know like - just to - well, in the street where I lived in Duke
 Road, well - whatever you can think of - we were young. There were nobody - no other children in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, various. One of them hoops, you know, and a stick or - an old tyre or something like that you kn
ow. I used to like - when I was indoors I liked playing with soldiers and all that. I used to get boxes of soldiers - sometimes given to me like at Christmastime and that. And I had 'em right 'til I left my grann}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 's. And - I used to have 'em on the table and I used to talk you know, set 'em - set 'em out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Your parents didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you belong to any youth organisations before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about your free time while you were still at school, did you have any hobbies, did you keep pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, I don't - I've never had any - pets in me -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Pocket money. Me granny very likely give me a penny or - something like that, perhaps a - I don't think that me father ever given me - I had a brother, the one who - alive now, he's seventy-five, I remember him giving me a - a few pence you know, now -
 for cleaning his buttons, when he went into the Army, he used to come home on leave. Used to clean his buttons and his - boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What used to happen to these guineas you used to get when you were at hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I give them to me granny. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you take part in any sports at all at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Oh well, that's when I lived - where was that - I think it was in Easter Street, Clerkenwell, I went home. Of course when I used to - like do the work and that, down on the Saturday - used 
to see the boys and - used to take me like - round Beatty waterworks, up the Rosebery Avenue there, and we used to play it from one street to the other, right across the main road. One }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 woul}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 d be over the other side and the other one this side. I mean to say you couldn't play like it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I walked for mile - I do now. I - I walk for miles an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 
d miles. I go - far as Eltham. R}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 ochester. Right out there and walk home again. Sometimes start at ten in the morning and very likely get h
ome about eleven o'clock at night. And walking all the time. Very likely have a cup of tea, and a sandwich, and that'd be me lot 'til I got home. That's all I eat and you know drink. I didn't hardly seem to feel hungry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And you used to like walking as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did you used to walk as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well I remember I used to walk - over Blackfriars bridge and out you know from - Duke Road, right round by the Elephant and St George's Road, over - back over Westminster, the Emba
nkment and - back home again. I - you know, I used to have imagination that was - in the Army, and - it used to be in my mind - I knew that I'd never get in. I tried to join the Navy, in the 1914 war, with the - with a friend of mine, and the - Colour Ser
geant, he said, if - get a bit of - dung in your shoes and get a bit bigger you can come back and see us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You would really like to have been in the Army would you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was this because you admired your father do you think at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about cinemas or theatres while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
I used to go to - on a Saturday - sometimes - you know, like - sometimes, when I was with me granny - I used to go - used to cost a penny. Euston cinema. Euston Road. Cowboys and Indians. We used to go crackers over them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you ever get in to theatres or concerts or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Once the school - me cousin was acting as Little John, he's bigger than me, and I was acting the Robin Hood. And we were 
rehearsing like for Christmas show - and it got - we started going up a bit rough, so we - we got slung out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Now how did you get on at school, did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, very nice, yes. Yes, teachers, I give 'em - me teacher, first teacher I ever
 - when I went in the infants, name of Miss Milligan. Then another one, Miss Walpole, when I went up higher. And - A Miss Brown. But all we was learning all the time was like - woodcarving, basketwork and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564  mat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 making.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 This was a cripple school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you ever go to a normal board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Could you tell us about this school, how old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I must have been about - five and a half. About five and a half when I first went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What time did you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Oh - we used to have to wait for - ambulance, the bottom of the street where I lived. And if you walked you got in trouble. Told off. And we used to pay - I think a penny - for our dinners. We used to have hot m
eal, like lunch - about eleven o'clock. I don't like milk. I used to give it to somebody else. We had dinner like - different things each day, up to - Friday. And when it was rice pudding I wouldn't eat it. They used to make me sit at the table, wait 'til
 they was going home, with that rice pudding in front of me. And I've never ate rice pudding from that day to this. Can't stand it. I don't like milk, so I have condensed milk for my tea. Well me gran brought me up on that. Condensed milk.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you go there for the full day right from the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What time did it start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well it started about - half past nine - 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What kind of school was it, what was the proper name of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Parsnal Edwards'. Yes. I say it was this R. Edwards. Parson Edwards. And they called it - St Mary's Wall now. It's in Woburn Place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was it mixed, boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Used to have girls in the same class with us. Some was - crippled and some was like - worse
 than me with their back and - you know, some a bit -
