\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well he had his daughter - in the shop, his wife, and another - chap. And I - got on all right with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So it was more or less a family concern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Sometimes I used to take two little - they had two girls. So}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 
metimes I'd take 'em out to Kens}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 ington Park, you know, for an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you like this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did the job alter your attitude to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How long did you stay at this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh about - two years. Over two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did you go after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I think I went to a job at Winchester. Aerodrome work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What year did you start there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 About 19 - 19 - 17 I think it was, 1916, 1917, between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What were you doing on this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I used to make the tea when I first went there like. Yes. We had a lot of Ger
man prisoners of war - there. And - sometimes I was in charge of a couple of - 'cos there was only - some of what I had was only - termed prison like - German from here. One come from Shepherds Bush and one come - Mile End.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 They had lived in England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes. They - they had two - cages, one for the - the Germans that - was taken prisoners, and these interned. And - any road I - got up to be a painter and glaziers labourer. And then I started learning how to mix paints and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How long did you do this sort of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I think I had it for about - nine months. I think I had about nine months. And then I come home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So that would bring you up more or less to the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. I went away to another job - at E}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6575419\charrsid6116564 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 ston on Green, Oxfordshire. And I know the war ended while I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You were doing the same sort of work there were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about your work since 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, City of London Corporation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You started just after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I was selling papers in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How long did you sell papers for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - just after the last war - like, first war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How long were you selling papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh, 'til - just before this war started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 About '38?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 '38 - '39 - '38. Any road I - give that up, the blackout and that, and I - joined the City of London - A.R.P. In between that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Was that a full time job in the A.R.P.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 YES. In between that - like they used to give you a month in the A.R.O. and a month - doing oth
er work like - a dustman or something, I wasn't supposed to carry anything on me back, but I - I used to manage it you know, to get along. Infact some of them tins used to go about - hundredweight and a half. YES. I used to - had to get up two steps on th
e - truck. But I used to manage it you know. I used to enjoy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What did you do after the war when the A.R.P. finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I was still on there and - I had this migraine -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or family at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, only like me sisters - used to - well we used to all have to do a bit of - work like, everybody had their own - jobs to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But you didn't have any grown ups, any neighbours or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well she was in - died of cancer. She was - I believe forty-nine when she died. Champion Hill - Dulwich. I used to go and see her sometimes but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You don't remember her being ill at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No neighbours helped or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I was - I was living with me granny, I used to go - from - Euston to - Champion Hill where she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have many relatives living round about where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, I got a
 big - very big family - I had. Wires, Carol, my mother's name was - when she was single her name was Caroll, her father - her father come from - Ireland, County Down. My grandmother was born here, but she had Irish parents. On me father's side was like -
 he was London people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So you had relatives from both sides of the family living in the neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, but I had aunt lived opposite where we lived in - in St Gabriel Street, Elephant and Castle. And
 - used to go across to see you know - sometimes they'd have a - a ding-dong on a Saturday night you know. But - I was only young at the time. About - thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 This is where your parents would usually see their relatives though, they'd go round each other's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes. Used to all gather at Christmastime. I had a - aunt, was well off, her husband was a rubber merchant, and he used to tell us tales about - when he was young, when he had no boots and - and he used to stand on his hands to he peop
le go by with the horses - traps then. They'd throw him ha'pennies and all that. Go round dustbins. Used to tell us all these tales at Christmastime. He worked himself up to be - well nearly a millionaire. He used to tell us the tale. He used to drink whe
n he was young man, but he knocked it - knocked it all on the head, only used to drink lemonade. But you could have what you liked.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your parents have any friends, or did they keep to their relatives mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well they'd be - they all seemed t
o keep to theirselves. But people used to mix, you know - used to have sing-songs, on a night time and - when we lived in rough quarters - in Seymour Street - sit on the doorsteps at twelve o'clock at night, all sing you know, they - people used to mix in
 with one another. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 That was just all the neighbours having a sing-song?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Like twelve, one o'clock in the morning. 'Cos the pubs never used to turn out - 'til twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You'd get a whole street more or less joining in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. You know, people were willing to help one an other then. It ain't like today, you - you don't know who your friends are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were these friends or neighbours ever invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, well just your family. Or their - their - their families and all that. I can't remember any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would friends call casually without invitation or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
No, just call in you know. Just dropped in. And - my granny used to take me - when I lived in - Seymour Street, Drum Crescent it was - used to take me ove
r the Elephant, I used to think it was wonderful, going through the City on a bus. And the - the - you know, all ashphalt then at the time, and see these cleaners washing it all down, you wouldn't see a tram ticket or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would neighbours drop in without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well had - not - not neighbours but you - your own - relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
You've told us something of peoples amusements in those days, did they do anything else apart from having a sing-song, did they play any games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I've seen people - well, you know, holiday times, in the streets - skipping ropes. Big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid484384\charrsid6116564 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564  what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid484384\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
names, even the women all used to get in and they - they - the old barrel organs - as well I - have a man come round or - pay him to come round and p
lay there or they used to go round the - public houses, play outside. Used to have - well, pay one of them to come round - and play the organ. Well like go to - Blackheath or - Hampstead Heath, somewhere like that. You know, the old - you know, the old po
ny and trap.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about when you had a bit of a ding-dong in the house, would you have any games then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
No, just singing - all singing you know, like - the old songs like - Down at the Old Bull and Bush and - I wouldn't leave my little wooden hut for you. Yes. Well - I heard them the other week when I was - down at Ramsgate. They sung all the old songs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 They're still popular in pub sing-songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Many people divide society into different social groups, at that time before 1918 did
 you think of some people belonging to one social group and some to another, were you conscious of this at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well yes, like we had a - when I lived in - Dukkes Road, just off the Euston Road there, a Mr - Davies, he was the Mayor of St Pancras. An
d he would be very friendly with my - uncles, you know, the rubb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid484384\charrsid6116564 er merchant. And Mr Hopkins, Con}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
servative. But never used to have like say to any of us. See they're different - class - different class of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What would you say the different social groups were in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well there were the poor, middle class and the - the upper class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What sort of people would you put in the poorer class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - people who had big families and - all had to go out to work and very likely two job
s or something like that, you know, and - used to be - they ad to go to the - Relieving Officer to get - you know, food for the children and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Who would you put in the middle class then, what sort of jobs would you say were middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Middle class, well there was - what we used to call snobs. You know - I'd sooner have more dealings with a - the high class people, than I would with the middle class. 'Cos I mean to say - their place was like - they was like the guv'nors, today. That's l
ike working in a factory and he was the boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about the schoolteachers, where would you put them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I think they were very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Which class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - you might say there was - just above the poor class you know. But you wouldn't c
all 'em middle class you know. Very nice - well where I went to school - Parsonal Edward's - cripple school - we had nurses and doctors at the school. And - they was very very nice to us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where would you put a doctor in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh I think t
he doctors were very good. I reckon they're above the doctors of today. I think - and I think they - took more interest in a patient, than what these doctors do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would they be middle class or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, they'd be - say middle class, some'd be - well paid men and some'd be - just ordinary you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about the local clergyman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I don't remember much about him, I - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564 I used to go to Sunday school, 
\lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 cos granny - granny used to make me go round St Pancras church, just off the Euston Road there. I was christened there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, everybody the same. You had to - sir or - it was a man, or - madam. Take your hat off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Who would you say sir or madam to in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Anybody you know, but - barring like your own class of people. You - just - like me - they didn't - want all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So it would be anyone slightly above working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you remember if anyone ever used to call your parents sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
No, no, no. Just call like - me - me mother's name was Mary, they used to call her - puddles. Me - me father's was name - Horace, they used to call him Harry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Who would you say were the most important people in the district where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Most important. I can't - there was the landlord or what - and we had, you know, respect for - like the police. We had to respect for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What sort of people would you say went to church in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well there was the - I say - poor class and rich class and took - like a different - parts of the - they used to have - their own - like society together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How about the chapel, were they much the same or was there any difference in chapel people do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, I don't think there was any - that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or were there different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well there was, som
e got more than others, you know. Like - I say, when I went home to my mother I was about - between nine and ten I left my granny. And - first time I knew what it was to be hungry. But - when I lived with my granny you might as well say - well I was livin
g in the middle class because - always had plenty to eat and - good clothes and - I remember a velvet suit I used to wear, with a lace collar, lace on the sleeves, you know, buckle shoes and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So granny was quite well off was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well, s
he was - her daughter used to - see that she - like me mother could have been the same if she'd have liked to have left me father. They didn't like him, so - she would have got a lot more help than what she did. If it wasn't for him. As I tell, he was ver
y nasty man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, well there was - rough families and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What sort of thing would make you say a family were a rough lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well they used to fight between one another and 
- use bad language and all that sort of thing. See? Now we were taught not to - swear or anything like that. Or if we got a bit too noisy we were brought up and sent to bed. Other people wouldn't take no notice of their children do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 This was more a matter of behaviour than money then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different social groups, did they treat everyone much the same or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Me mother used to - as I told you 
this before, she worked for the Duchess of Marlborough. And - Sir Ernest Kraut. And - I think these sort of people used to think more of the working class people like then. And - I believe once she took me to go and see - in Bedford - Bedford Square, wher
e they had a place. I remember her giving me a blanc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 manage and - 'course I'd - I'd been at home a decent while then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you remember this sort of distinction between craftsmen and labourers, was there any sort of social distinction there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, don't think there was. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 They'd all much in together would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, she was a - a woman that - mixed with anybody. She was - hardworking and - she'd do anything for anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you think it was possible at that time to move from one social group to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well you had to - be in the money to - to get that. I doubt if my mother would have - took any notice of things like that. Me fath
er might but - not me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
You mean into the family? No. Oh yes. Well I did have a lady - used to send me - certain times of the year I had boxes of butterscotch, Scou
t books, if I wanted a overcoat - Miss Isaacs. Or - I don't know whether she was a Lady or what. And - she wanted me to go - spend a holiday. But - I didn't like being away from home - even when I was in hospital - I thought that - cry. I was at seaside, 
oh for a long time, and I cried all the time I was there. I can remember all them things. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you remember seeing policemen around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Oh every corner. Yes. Used to come in twos, and - not only shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 doors, they
 used to try - they used to test your - street door to see if it was shut. All the way round. Of course there - there wasn't all that violence then. No, if you - such a thing like murder, it was a great thing, used to be in the paper. Like - I don't know 
whether - when Crippin was caught, how they made such a - show of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What did you think of the police in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I think they were wonderful men. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How do you think they treated people on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - if you - behaved your
self, if you were drunk, and you started going violent, then they'd - get the old - barrow they used to have with - two wheels on, used to put 'em on the barrow and strap 'em on it, go down the police court.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How did they treat you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Wel
l they - very nice you know. Like - you wanted to go across the road or anything like that - and - making a bit of noise that wouldn't interfere with us. They were just playing - you were playing football in the street they may stop you. Or breaking windo
ws or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Your home was rented, did you see anything of the landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
I can't - I can't remember the landlord. But - I know it used to be about - three and six a week. For room what I've got now - would cost you about - five to six pounds a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What did you feel about him as a landlord, was he a good landlord or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I don't remember him see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, they did, as - as I said. Me father never helped at all. Only me mother. She did two or three jobs.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Were you conscious of this as a child or did you just realize it in later life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well - we didn't think much of it then. But - no, we realized it later on. And we only 
wished we had her here so as that - we could have done something for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your mother ever get any help from the Guardians or the Parish or anywhere like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I don't think she ever went - me father used to go sometimes. And they used 
to tell him he - like - have to chop wood or something like that. Well he was such a lazy man that - used to have the - what do you call 'em - the - relieving officer used to come round and see - look in your cupboards, see if you had any food there or an
ything like that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 How did the Relieving Officers treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well they - wouldn't give you much you know. They may give you a ticket to go and get - like milk, tea, or - margarine, whatever it was, butter. Just a few things to last a couple of days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What was their attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well they - hint that my father should have gone to work you know. But - I can't remember him ever going to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But you say he was in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, he was in the Army, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So he got paid his wages for being in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well, he had to - big grants, because he told 'em what he was before the - well he was brought up in the profession, his father was a - a butcher, also a wheelwright. He was; brought up in that sort of way. He was left a big bu
siness. And it went broke. And when he went in the Army - and I can remember the 1914 war when he wrote - to the people you know, the - what do you call 'em, the - where they have their depots - Aldershot or somewhere, and they give him a grant for so man
y - pounds to start off his business again. I remember him having that done to him twice. But all he done was gamble it and get rid of it that way, or drink it away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So he used to go in the Army for a while and come out again did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well he went - he joined the - Army Battery Corps. He went to France and got this job, then he joined the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 This was in 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Then he joined the - A.S.C. I believe it was. He went across again and got discharged again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 In this time before 1914 what was he doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. From 19 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 From about 1900 to 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I can only remember him from about - 1910, see. And I can't remember his doing - any work or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 So he was more or less unemployed during that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 He had left the Army by 1910 had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. But he was - he was in the Army like when the Boer war was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And came out of the Army sometime after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 After, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 And didn't work until 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. Well I remember going to
 see him. 'Cos he must have been in the Army when I - went back home, in 1910 or - or 'll, going to Aldershot to see him with me mother. So he left after that. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Just a couple of years before the war started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 When there was someone in the district that people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well people used to - ignore 'em, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Some people tell us in those days there used to be a thing called rough music, th
at people that they didn't like, a particular neighbour, for some reason, they'd all go and bang drums and tins outside their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh no, I don't remember anything like that, no. No. They just used to - walk by and ignore 'em. So like they move - w
ell - places were easy to get then. Very likely the people might - move away. Within a couple of months or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You worked for the City of London Corporation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. From 1939.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Looking back over the various jobs you've done since you've left school, would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
What I never done? Yes, I would have liked to have been a carpenter. At school see the - we never done much lessons at school, all we done was like - basketwork when I was
 there, because I was mostly in hospital you know, in and out. Basketwork, mat making - bit of woodcarving and - such things as that. But lessons, we never - I mean - when I left school - I couldn't tell the time. And - I learnt myself how to write. Tell 
the time. Well, learnt myself everything, how to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, I had one - I don't think it wasted about - a month or six weeks, as an apprentice - in Royal Lane, in the City. That was dur}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
 the 1940, I don't what I - job I - job after job like. When I first left school, I worked in a boot shop. Nine shillings a week. Used to do a twelve hour a day. Well I had about - sixteen on a Saturday and about - eighteen or so on a - I me
an - on a Friday sixteen, on a Saturday well I had eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you belong to any trade union or anything like this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No, I belonged to one in me last job, the City of London Corporation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you take part in any of the activities at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well we had one - no, I never took no notice - like shop stewards or anything like that. We had one strike when I was on it. That was over - Tower Bridge - the Mayor of Tower Bridge had a bit of a dispute. And instead of letting them get on with 
it they called all us out on strike. We was out for two weeks, and we had to go back again - without a penny. We - we didn't - we-l we didn't want to go out on strike at all, only - Secretary or the - or the Treasurer of the union called us out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Well I - worked in a - glassblowers, and the gov'nor of the firm was a German. Mr Stern. And I reckon he had a lot of interest in his workers. But - anywhere else, like the City of London Corporation - was very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Do you feel that there are any divisions of interest between the workers themselves, different groups of workers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes, you did find it you know like - had the little - groups of men and another group. Never used - never used to mix together you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Some people say that in those days there was a big division between the trained craftsmen and other workers did you feel this or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
You mean when I was working that I - I - enjoyed it or anything like that? Yes. Yes, I used to like working, I mean to say - I used to do plenty of overtime and - you know - I used to enjoy it, I used to like work you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 From the time you started work up until 1918 did you continue to live at home during that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 19 - after I left school, yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You still lived at your own home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 I still lived at - but I can remember you know - that practically most of the time - I was still in - still going in and out of hospital.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Or your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you spend your Sundays and differently, did you still go to Sunday school and things like this after you started work or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, I don't think I did ever go to - go to - like football or - things like that, sports, used to go like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you take any interest in politics at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, never interested me. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
You say you lived at home after you started work, did you change your activities at all from the sort of things you did when you were at school, did you start play-ing different games or doing different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
Yes, well I - I wasn't allowed to take - part - in school, any football, I just had to watch. See I had this big jacket on underneath me what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 name, and they wouldn't allow - just though I was a w
eakling, supposed to have been. And - I made sure when I left school that I was going to play it all and I was going to - was going to in me own - sort of self that I could things that they didn't think that I could do. I don't know, every}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 time I seemed to go there, it was an operation, something like that. Or - maybe they was right you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But you said after you left school you threw this jacket off and started playing football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 What did the doctors say about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 We
ll I never went back no more. I went - oh - about - just after the - this war, I went there when I had this - migraine and - they asked me questions, and I told 'em about that and about the jacket. They didn't seem to - take no notice, they didn't seem to
 have any records of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 You told me from your first job you used to have about one and six a week to spend for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Where did you used to go in the evenings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well used to go to the - South London - you know, like - on 
a Saturday - we used to go to South London for a show, or - that used to cost about - tuppence. Pictures used to be a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Who did you used to go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Well I used to have a mate. Lived opposite of me, he had about - twelve brothers, and - I t
hink in the 1914 war there was about ten of 'em killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you make any new friends at this time or were they mainly people you knew already?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Oh, people that I knew, from way - you know, back. - I had a cousin - had a paper stand over in - outside Euston s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4217230\charrsid6116564 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 ation. I used to go and help him sometimes - we were brought up together me and him. And he was more my friend than - anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you used to take your friends home at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your parents meet your friends at all, the friends you made after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 
No, I - I never even took 'em home you know, like - introduced 'em. Just - went out and met them and that, end on the night time just said - good night and that was that. 'Til the next day or whenever it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did your parent still expect to know where you were going when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Did you have any special time for being back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 Before I was fourteen, yes. Had to be in by about nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6826951 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 But not after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12791563 FJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4071099\charrsid6116564 No.
\par }}